{
  "stem": "3012.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So what we did was that we ripped off part of our undershirt, which was strictly forbidden, and put it around her leg during the day, when there were no [GERMAN] When the [GERMAN] came, then it was torn off, hidden somewhere, wherever we could.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And hoping for the best, that Mengele or the person who is doing the selection-- because there were selections and [GERMAN] all the time-- will not notice it.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then she developed some kind of a boil under her arm.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was getting from bad to worse.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it looked just horrendous and painful.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the selection, and the [GERMAN] and time was going.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, as time progressed it was getting worse and worse.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we really didn't know what to do.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then one day, following a very long selection, and this was probably-- I have to say another thing about my mother.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When she came to pick me up at the revier, happened to be on the 20th of July, 1944.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And as we learned later, that was the day of the botched assassination attempt by Count Stauffenberg and his partners against Hitler.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Mother, before dawn, started on her journey.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She had her own mission.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And sneaking her way as gingerly as she could from her block to the revier, and hoping for the best that she's not caught by the guard.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because if anybody left the latrine area at night, that person could be shot on the spot.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, there were no questions in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Only shootings, or people being taken away.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, as a matter of fact, she was stopped by the guard, who happened to be a regular army man.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm not saying that the army is innocent, or was innocent.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I'm not saying that.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
